# ContextLite: RAG Systems Were a Mistake

⚡ **0.3ms** response time (vs 30-50ms for vector DBs) | 🎯 **Provably optimal** results | 💰 **$0** ongoing costs | 🔒 **100% local**

Replace slow, approximate vector databases with mathematically optimal context selection. ContextLite delivers lightning-fast, precise results without the complexity and costs of traditional vector database solutions.

## Why Vector Databases Are Obsolete

| Feature | ContextLite | Vector DBs |
|---------|-------------|------------|
| **Response Time** | ⚡ 0.3ms | 🐌 30-50ms |
| **Accuracy** | 🎯 Mathematically optimal | 📊 Approximate similarity |
| **Monthly Costs** | 💰 $0 (local) | 💸 $300-500+ (cloud) |
| **Data Privacy** | 🔒 100% local | ☁️ Uploaded to cloud |
| **Setup Time** | ⚡ 30 seconds | 🕐 Hours/days |

## 🆕 Enterprise Features

✨ **Professional workspace isolation, resource management, and load balancing for enterprise AI development.**

## Core Features

- **� SMT Optimization**: Mathematical precision instead of probabilistic approximations
- **🔥 Ultra-Fast**: Sub-millisecond query responses with optimized algorithms
- **🚀 Zero Dependencies**: Single Windows executable with no external services
- **🛡️ Enterprise Ready**: Multi-tenancy, clustering, and advanced licensing
- **⚡ REST API**: Easy integration with any language or framework
- **📊 Analytics**: Real-time performance monitoring and usage statistics

## Installation

After installation, ContextLite will be available as the `contextlite` command:

```
contextlite --help
contextlite --port 8080
```

## Quick Start

1. Start the server: `contextlite --port 8080`
2. Add documents via REST API
3. Query for relevant content
4. Get mathematically optimal results in 0.3ms

Visit https://docs.contextlite.com for complete documentation.

**Download other platforms:** https://huggingface.co/spaces/MikeKuykendall/contextlite-download

## Package Notes

This Chocolatey package installs the ContextLite binary and makes it available system-wide via PATH. Perfect for Windows developers who need the fastest context retrieval solution.
